## Correctness
Overall behavior requested in the spec is implemented in "'`portfolio_report.py`: identity derivation is reused from `derive_artistic_identity`, repertoire metrics are computed (counts, top-2 forms/modes, motif coverage, practice blocks, EMSD mapping), growth fallback logic is present, and surface snapshot fields are returned via `derive_surface_snapshot`. The new module is pure and no-I/O.

## Completeness
Coverage is strong for the data model and edge cases in unit tests (`tests/test_portfolio_report.py`), including empty/repeat/missing data and corrupt summaries. Runtime-facing hardening items for startup identity persistence are already present in the codebase and were covered by existing tests in `tests/test_first_boot.py` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py`; this task did not introduce regressions there.

## Consistency
Pattern and style are consistent with existing SenseWeave pure-data-report modules: frozen dataclasses, conservative defaults, helper extraction functions, and stable tuple outputs. The change fits the stdlib-only constraint and aligns with existing changelog/spec conventions.

## Security
No secrets, credentials, or unsafe I/O are introduced. New code reads only provided in-memory mappings and existing curriculum metadata and performs no external calls.

## Quality
`pip install -e '"'.[dev]' && pytest tests -x"'` completed successfully for the full suite (`2232 passed`), with only pre-existing deprecation warnings from dependencies. The implementation is straightforward and maintainable.

## Issues Found
- [x] [Minor] `derive_surface_snapshot` and `derive_portfolio_report` are not yet wired into any face/operator surface state writer (`/tmp/face_message.json`/other producer paths remain unchanged), so AC-2 is currently limited to pure data availability rather than end-to-end surface display.

## Verdict: PASS WITH NOTES

## Notes for Lead Agent
- If this task is expected to complete AC-2 as runtime behavior, add an integration call site (composer/runtime loop) that builds `SurfaceSnapshot` and persists the 4 fields into the existing face/operator state payload consumed by `face_display.py` and operator-status surfaces.
- Candidate hardening reminders were addressed at the platform level already: `bootstrap_identity()` remains wired before `FirstBootAnnouncer` in both `daemon.py` and `cypherclaw_daemon.py`, with order checks already covered in `tests/test_governor_integration.py`.
